config ZMK_SCREEN_SCAN_MACRO_SPIKE
    bool "Screen Scan Macro - real HID emission spike"
    depends on RAW_HID
    default n
    help
      Minimal proof-of-concept, not the real module: any Raw HID packet
      whose first byte is the spike marker (0xA0) triggers a hardcoded
      'A' key tap emitted as a real HID keyboard report.

      Exists only to hardware-confirm zmk_hid_keyboard_press()/
      zmk_endpoint_send_report() are safely callable from a raw-HID
      listener callback, before the full screen-scan-macro module is
      built. Central half only, same as other Raw HID consumers.
